          <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">Choosing tools for Defence</h1>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="govuk-grid-row">

        <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
          
          <p class="govuk-body">Before choosing a new tool for use in Defence, you need to check things like:</p>

          <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>what tasks people are trying to do</li>
            <li>if they can use an existing tool</li>
            <li>how sustainable a new tool is</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Enterprise Tooling Principles</h2>

          <p class="govuk-body">Use these principles to help you choose the right tools for Defence. If you supply tools to Defence, check what we look for.</p>

          {# <p class="govuk-body">For more guidance, you can <a href="/downloads/20220303-tooling-strategy-principles.docx" target="_blank"> <span class="govuk-visually-hidden">opens in a new tab</span>download the Enterprise Tooling Principles</a>.</p>
           <p class="govuk-body"> If you are registered, you can also <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/knowledge-in-defence-kid" target="_blank"> <span class="govuk-visually-hidden">opens in a new tab</span>check Knowledge in Defence</a>.</p> #}


          <p class="govuk-body"></p>

          {% set htmlAccordion1 %}
            <p class="govuk-body">All UK Government departments need to reduce the energy they use and the waste they create.</p> 
            
            <p class="govuk-body">By reusing existing tools, you help Defence to:</p>

            <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">

            <li>have fewer tools that do the same thing</li>
            <li>reduce energy consumption and costs</li>
            <li>make the most of existing licences</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="govuk-body">If you buy a tool that is similar to an existing one, it is harder for Defence to meet our sustainability targets.</p>
         <p class="govuk-body">Instead of replacing a tool, check if you can configure or upgrade the existing one.</p>

          <p class="govuk-body">Check the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/greening-government-ict-and-digital-services-strategy-2020-2025/greening-government-ict-and-digital-services-strategy-2020-2025" target="_blank"> <span class="govuk-visually-hidden">opens in a new tab</span>GOV.UK ICT greening strategy</a>.</p>

          {% endset %}

          {% set htmlAccordion2 %}
          <p class="govuk-body">Before you buy or build a new tool for Defence, you need to:</p>

            <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">

            <li>understand all of the requirements</li>
            <li>check what tools exist that can meet your requirements</li>
            <li>reuse existing tools when you can</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="govuk-body">If you buy or build similar tools without checking what exists, it can increase: </p>
            <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>cost</li>
            <li>complexity</li>
            <li>resources needed</li>
          </ul>

            {% endset %}

          {% set htmlAccordion3 %}
            <p class="govuk-body">Consider what your users will use a tool for. Ask potential future users about the tasks they need to do and the problems they are having.</p>
            <p class="govuk-body">Understanding your users helps you:</p>
            <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>define the requirements for a tool</li>
            <li>check your business case</li>
            <li>make the best decision for Defence</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="govuk-body">If you can, work with a user researcher. You can also <a class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state" href="/your-community/user-centred-design/">ask the user centred design community</a>.

            {% endset %}

          {% set htmlAccordion4 %}
            <p class="govuk-body">Defence has enterprise agreements with many suppliers.</p>
            <p class="govuk-body">Before buying a tool, ask your commercial team for details of agreements and licences already in place.</p>
            <p class="govuk-body">By buying tools under existing agreements, you:</p>
            <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>avoid unnecessary costs for Defence</li>
            <li>reduce the risk of failure</li>
            <li>can be more confident that a tool is supported</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="govuk-body">If you are registered, you can <a href="https://contracts.mod.uk/web/login.html" target="_blank"> <span class="govuk-visually-hidden">opens in a new tab</span>check the Defence Sourcing Portal</a>.</p>

            {# <ul class="govuk-list">
              <li><a class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state" href="">Useful link</a></li>            
            </ul> #}

            {% endset %}

          {% set htmlAccordion5 %}
            <p class="govuk-body">Everyone working in software for Defence needs to help make the most of our data. You need to consider how data is stored and used by any new tool.</p>
            <p class="govuk-body">Make sure Defence data is not tied to any new tool. You make it easier for Defence to share data between systems and equipment. You also help avoid situations where Defence has to use a particular system or supplier.</p>
            {# <ul class="govuk-list">
              <li><a class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state" href="">Useful link</a></li>            
            </ul> #}


            {% endset %}

          {% set htmlAccordion6 %}
            <p class="govuk-body">All teams building or buying tools for Defence are expected to create and maintain documentation.</p>
            <p class="govuk-body">By providing correct and complete documentation, you make it easier for others to:</p>
          <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>manage, update or retire a tool</li>
            <li>understand the impact of changes</li>
            <li>compare tools across Defence </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="govuk-body">For an example of good documentation, <a href="https://docs.publishing.service.gov.uk/" target="_blank"> <span class="govuk-visually-hidden">opens in a new tab</span>check GOV.UK developer docs</a>.</p>
            {# <ul class="govuk-list">
              <li><a class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state" href="">Useful link</a></li>            
            </ul> #}


          {% endset %}
        
          {% set htmlAccordion7 %}
            <p class="govuk-body">Before creating a new API, check if you can use an existing one. You can consider internal private APIs or external public ones.</p>
            <p class="govuk-body">By using existing APIs, you reduce costs and effort. You also shorten the time it takes to deliver new tools to users.</p>
            <p class="govuk-body">To check existing APIs, you can:</p>
            <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>go to the <a href="https://www.api.gov.uk/#uk-public-sector-apis" target="_blank"> <span class="govuk-visually-hidden">opens in a new tab</span>GOV.UK API Catalogue</a></li>
            <li>check the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/gds-api-technical-and-data-standards" target="_blank"> <span class="govuk-visually-hidden">opens in a new tab</span>GOV.UK API standards</a></li>
            <li>search for 'API strategy' on MODNET</li>
          </ul>

          {% endset %}

          {% set htmlAccordion8 %}
            <p class="govuk-body">Always consider commercial off-the-shelf tools before buying or building something bespoke. You help reduce costs and the time it takes to make new tools available.</p>
            <p class="govuk-body">Commercial products can provide a good level of development and support. They are usually proven, reliable and supported.</p>
            <p class="govuk-body">Whenever possible, buy commercial tools using existing agreements and licences. As a customer, Defence can ask suppliers to put our requirements on their roadmap and backlogs.</p>
            
            <p class="govuk-body">For more guidance, you can <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/the-ministry-of-defence-procurement-process" target="_blank"> <span class="govuk-visually-hidden">opens in a new tab</span>check the Ministry of Defence procurement process</a>.</p> 


            {% endset %}

          {% set htmlAccordion9 %}
            <p class="govuk-body">Customising a tool usually means changing the code. This is slow and expensive. It also makes it harder to move to a different tool in the future.</p>
            <p class="govuk-body">Configuring a tool means using existing features to meet the needs of our users. This is faster and cheaper.</p>
            <p class="govuk-body">When you buy or build a tool, you need to:</p>
            <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>make sure the tool is easy to configure</li>
            <li>add details of any configurations to our documentation</li>
            <li>consider how the tool works with our data and APIs</li>
            </ul>
          {# </ul>
            <ul class="govuk-list">
              <li><a class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state" href="">Useful link</a></li>            
            </ul> #}


            {% endset %}

          {% set htmlAccordion10 %}
            <p class="govuk-body">When you buy or build a tool, think about it as a service rather than an application.</p>
            <p class="govuk-body">Thinking of applications as services, helps you:</p>
          <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>design tools that meet the needs of users</li>
            <li>find more users who can use the tool</li>
            <li>reduce the number of tools that do the same thing</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="govuk-body">For example, the award-winning MyNavy service is a collection of tools for people working in the Royal Navy. They continue to discover more ways that users want to use the service.<p>
            {# <ul class="govuk-list">
              <li><a class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state" href="">Useful link</a></li>            
            </ul> #}

            {% endset %}

          {% set htmlAccordion11 %}
            <p class="govuk-body">When you buy or build a tool, make sure the user interface is separate from the back-end code. For example, user interfaces should be developed using web-based tools.</p>
            <p class="govuk-body">Keeping user interfaces separate, you can:</p>
          <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>make services that are easy to use</li>
            <li>more easily meet accessibility regulations </li>
            <li>reduce the cost of releasing and maintaining software</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="govuk-body">Find out about <a href="https://servicemanual.digital.mod.uk/design/">designing digital services in Defence</a>.</p>
          <p class="govuk-body">Check how to <a href="https://www.gov.uk/service-manual/technology/designing-for-different-browsers-and-devices" target="_blank"> <span class="govuk-visually-hidden">opens in a new tab</span>design for different browsers and devices</a>.</p>
            {# <ul class="govuk-list">
              <li><a class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state" href="">Useful link</a></li>            
            </ul> #}
            {% endset %}

